Code:
s = "abcd"
print(s[::-1])
👉 Output:
dcba
🧠 Concept: Slicing

Python slicing format:

s[start : stop : step]
What does [::-1] mean?
s[::-1]
start → not given → default (end of string)
stop → not given → default (before beginning)
step = -1 → move backward
🔁 How it works

String:

a   b   c   d
0   1   2   3

Reverse traversal:

d → c → b → a
🔥 Internally Python does:
Start from last index → d
Move one step backward (-1)
Keep going until beginning
✅ Equivalent loop
s = "abcd"

for i in range(len(s)-1, -1, -1):
    print(s[i], end="")

👉 Output:

dcba
Key Idea

👉 [::-1] = reverse the string

🔥 More examples
s = "python"

print(s[::-1])   # nohtyp
print(s[::1])    # python
print(s[::2])    # pto (skip 1 char)
🚀 Easy Rule
step = 1 → forward
step = -1 → backward
👉 So:

[::-1] → reverse
